  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NIHR ACT Alliance IRQ151 Support to Displaced People and hosts in Iraq</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is part of the ACT IRQ151 appeal in Iraq. This project will bring about significant change to the lives of those in Iraq affected by the most recent humanitarian crisis, specifically those the needs of those in Qayyarah, an area recently re-taken from ISIS by the Iraq security forces. NIHR carried out an assessment in some villages surrounding Qayyarah, and we have coordinated with the WFP cluster contact. We have selected a village which has not received any support from other agencies and also where we are able to provide for all residents of the village.  NIHR identified that 80 families remained there during the liberation process, and 113 escaped and have since returned. NIHR are expecting that by the time the distribution takes place in October further families will have returned so costs are included for an additional 33 households.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will provide unconditional cash transfers in Ausaja village in Qayyarah, recently re-taken by Iraqi forces. $50 will be given per person per household.</narrative>
  </description>
